    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>With this plugin you can enable your users to switch website between Night Mode and normal style smoothly to improve the readability of text, images and videos.</p>\n<p>Reading website content at night time can be difficult. Help your visitors read more articles, spend more time on your website and protect their eyes from being hurt.</p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload <code>wp-night-mode</code> to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress</li>\n<li>Use <code>wp-night-mode</code> class on any element (for example Menu item) or <code>[wp-night-mode-button]</code> shortcode to show Night Mode toggle button</li>\n<li>Shortcode options:\n<ul>\n<li>&#8220;style&#8221; option, for Toggle Style. Use it like this: <code>[wp-night-mode-button style=\"4\"]</code></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Go to Customizer and set styles for Night Mode</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>Version History</h4>\n<p>Refer to the <a href=\"https://github.com/markoarula/wp-night-mode\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">GitHub</a> for more information regarding the latest changes.</p>\n"
    },
    "short_description": "Allow users to change the website style while reading at night, enabling them to easily read and spend more time on your site.",
